sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: PAXgene blood RNA tubes were left at room temperaturee to defrost (4 hours) while mixing by inversion.
sample_growth_protocol_ch1: Whole blood was collected in PAXgene blood RNA tubes, mixed by inversion 10X and stored at -80C.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated in accordance with the PAXgene blood RNA isolation (QIAGEN) procedure using the QIAcube workstation.
sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)
sample_hyb_protocol: Standard Affymetrix GeneAtlas® Hybridization, Wash, and Stain Kit.
sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: PAXgene blood RNA tubes were left at room temperaturee to defrost (4 hours) while mixing by inversion.
sample_growth_protocol_ch1: Whole blood was collected in PAXgene blood RNA tubes, mixed by inversion 10X and stored at -80C.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated in accordance with the PAXgene blood RNA isolation (QIAGEN) procedure using the QIAcube workstation.
sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)
sample_hyb_protocol: Standard Affymetrix GeneAtlas® Hybridization, Wash, and Stain Kit.

sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)

sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_hyb_protocol: Standard Affymetrix GeneAtlas® Hybridization, Wash, and Stain Kit.
sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)
sample_hyb_protocol: Standard Affymetrix GeneAtlas® Hybridization, Wash, and Stain Kit.
sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated in accordance with the PAXgene blood RNA isolation (QIAGEN) procedure using the QIAcube workstation.
sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)

sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)

sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_hyb_protocol: Standard Affymetrix GeneAtlas® Hybridization, Wash, and Stain Kit.
sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)
sample_hyb_protocol: Standard Affymetrix GeneAtlas® Hybridization, Wash, and Stain Kit.
sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated in accordance with the PAXgene blood RNA isolation (QIAGEN) procedure using the QIAcube workstation.
sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)

sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.

sample_label_protocol_ch1: 100ng total RNA was labeled using standard GeneChip® 3' IVT Express Kit (Affymetrix)

sample_description: blood gene expression data from healthy subjects and critically-ill patients.
sample_data_processing: Raw data scans (.CEL files) were read into the R language and environment for statistical computing (version 2.15.1; R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria; http://www.R-project.org/). Pre-processing and quality control was performed by using the Affy package version 1.36.1. Array data were background corrected by Robust Multi-array Average, quantiles-normalized and summarized by medianpolish using the expresso function. The resultant 49,386 probe intensities were filtered by means of a 0.5 variance cutoff using the genefilter method to recover 24,646 expressed probes. The occurrence of non-experimental chip effects was evaluated by means of the Surrogate Variable Analysis (R package version 3.4.0) and corrected by the empirical Bayes method ComBat.
